00:26:03.080 --> 00:26:04.760
Don't lose it. You're going to need it.

275
00:26:05.120 --> 00:26:06.280
Against infection.

276
00:26:06.800 --> 00:26:10.440
Knew a guy once. helmsman on U-491.
unfortunately already dead.

277
00:26:10.840 --> 00:26:13.200
He caught something
the night before he sailed.

278
00:26:13.280 --> 00:26:16.600
Itching got so bad.
he took my cheese-grater to it.

279
00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:17.600
No. really?

280
00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:19.240
True story!

281
00:26:21.720 --> 00:26:25.880
Something you need to know. Killer.
It's bad luck to take a virgin on board.

282
00:26:26.560 --> 00:26:28.680
You have to blow your load tonight.
for good luck!

283
00:26:29.720 --> 00:26:30.640
Come on lads.

284
00:26:31.000 --> 00:26:32.080
Let's christen the boat.

285
00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:37.920
They've got to break.
Or else it's bad luck.

286
00:26:39.800 --> 00:26:42.880
- Prepare soundings!
- Prepare soundings!

287
00:26:42.960 --> 00:26:44.000
Soundings!

288
00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:47.520
Soundings! In zero!

289
00:27:02.320 --> 00:27:03.800
Move! I'll do it.

290
00:27:22.560 --> 00:27:23.600
Holy shit!

291
00:27:23.880 --> 00:27:24.720
Fire extinguisher!

292
00:28:01.440 --> 00:28:02.920
I came to apologize to you.

293
00:28:05.640 --> 00:28:06.840
Maybe I was wrong.

294
00:28:09.080 --> 00:28:10.760
Maybe you shouldn't have made a statement.

295
00:28:19.320 --> 00:28:21.760
I felt better once I admitted it.

296
00:28:25.800 --> 00:28:27.080
That I am not a hero.

297
00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:32.120
If the boat had been sunk...

298
00:28:32.960 --> 00:28:34.640
nobody would know. right?

299
00:28:36.960 --> 00:28:38.920
No one would know whose fault it was.

300
00:28:39.400 --> 00:28:41.280
If that boat had gone down...

301
00:28:42.440 --> 00:28:44.120
then I'd have died a hero.

302
00:28:54.520 --> 00:28:55.640
Will you come?

303
00:28:57.840 --> 00:28:58.920
Tomorrow morning?

304
00:28:59.280 --> 00:29:00.400
Of course.

305
00:29:03.560 --> 00:29:05.280
Is there anything I can do for you?

306
00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:17.160
That's my mother's address.

307
00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:21.520
Could you write to her...

308
00:29:22.080 --> 00:29:23.800
that I took it like a man?

309
00:29:52.440 --> 00:29:54.120
It'll have to be rebuilt from scratch.

310
00:29:55.600 --> 00:29:58.720
I need new parts for this.
It'll take at least 24 hours.

311
00:29:58.880 --> 00:30:00.160
You'll do it tonight.

312
00:30:02.040 --> 00:30:03.360
Sir. that's impo...

313
00:30:03.440 --> 00:30:05.080
Give Miller a list of your requirements.

314
00:30:05.720 --> 00:30:07.960
He will also retrieve
your personal effects.

315
00:30:08.920 --> 00:30:09.760
My effects?

316
00:30:09.920 --> 00:30:12.840
You are being assigned to the radio room
of U-612 for this war cruise.

317
00:30:13.200 --> 00:30:14.320
With immediate effect.

318
00:30:15.640 --> 00:30:17.120
With permission. Sir.

319
00:30:17.640 --> 00:30:19.320
isn't there anybody else who could go?

320
00:30:19.760 --> 00:30:22.520
The assigned Petty Officer Radio is
in the hospital with severe burns.

321
00:30:22.600 --> 00:30:24.120
Your orders are to replace him.

322
00:30:24.200 --> 00:30:26.240
Or should I have you arrested
for refusal to serve?

323
00:30:26.320 --> 00:30:28.440
No! No.

324
00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:29.880
Good.

325
00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:32.800
Tell him the location of your dormitory.

326
00:30:33.440 --> 00:30:35.240
This boat will sail tomorrow on time.

327
00:30:35.640 --> 00:30:38.080
With you and a functioning radio.

328
00:30:40.800 --> 00:30:42.520
Sir. if I might request.

329
00:30:43.400 --> 00:30:45.720
Would it be possible
that my sister would bring my effects?

330
00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:47.080
She just arrived today.

331
00:30:47.440 --> 00:30:49.320
She works for Captain Gluck.

332
00:30:50.840 --> 00:30:53.000
It would help me with the work if she...

333
00:31:00.040 --> 00:31:00.920
I'm sorry.

334
00:31:06.800 --> 00:31:09.040
The radio operator is not
to leave the boat.

335
00:31:09.120 --> 00:31:10.400
A woman will bring his effects.

336
00:31:10.560 --> 00:31:11.360
But...

337
00:31:11.440 --> 00:31:12.960
Don't give me that superstitious nonsense.

338
00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:15.320
Just make sure that she doesn't
distract him from his work.

339
00:31:20.280 --> 00:31:21.760
Have a nice evening.

340
00:31:22.080 --> 00:31:23.160
And you.

341
00:31:27.240 --> 00:31:28.080
Miss Strasser.

342
00:31:30.400 --> 00:31:32.600
I haven't really introduced myself.

343
00:31:32.720 --> 00:31:33.720
Criminal Inspector Forster.

344
00:31:35.240 --> 00:31:36.200
Good evening.

345
00:31:37.360 --> 00:31:38.360
Well...

346
00:31:39.560 --> 00:31:41.920
Your first day
and you're the last to leave.

347
00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:45.080
No wonder your supervisor in Paris
was so sorry to see you leave.

348
00:31:46.680 --> 00:31:49.560
Oh. You must have read
my file very carefully then.

349
00:31:49.920 --> 00:31:51.920
I read all files. Bad habit.

350
00:31:52.400 --> 00:31:57.920
I told Gluck that it would be a crime
if you were wasted on mundane work.

351
00:31:58.080 --> 00:32:00.000
Ah. Thank you so much.

352
00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:03.280
Well. consider it my attempt
at an apology.

353
00:32:03.600 --> 00:32:04.560
For what?

354
00:32:04.680 --> 00:32:08.040
For making you think that I would question
your loyalty towards Germany.

355
00:32:09.400 --> 00:32:14.640
Maybe my loyalty is so big
because I grew up in Alsace

356
00:32:15.040 --> 00:32:17.840
and because I could only admire Germany
from a distance.

357
00:32:18.640 --> 00:32:22.400
As a German I always felt
like a stranger in France.

358
00:32:23.800 --> 00:32:24.800
You won't feel like this here.

359
00:32:25.160 --> 00:32:26.240
Miss Strasser?

360
00:32:27.200 --> 00:32:28.560
- I apologize.
- Yes?

361
00:32:29.280 --> 00:32:30.320
It's about your brother.

362
00:32:31.880 --> 00:32:32.720
Yes?

363
00:33:03.520 --> 00:33:06.920
So that's what it feels like
to fire a torpedo?

364
00:33:08.560 --> 00:33:10.000
Feels like fucking?

365
00:33:12.320 --> 00:33:13.400
That's right.

366
00:33:15.760 --> 00:33:17.200
At least afterwards.

367
00:33:21.080 --> 00:33:24.160
You son of a bitch! Stick it inside her!

368
00:33:25.080 --> 00:33:26.120
Already have!

369
00:33:26.800 --> 00:33:30.320
There he is! Come on. killer. Get her!

370
00:33:31.080 --> 00:33:33.400
Your dick knows where to go!

371
00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:40.040
I want one too.

372
00:34:10.720 --> 00:34:11.720
Thank you.

373
00:34:13.240 --> 00:34:14.080
Keep the change.

374
00:34:16.120 --> 00:34:17.000
Thanks.

375
00:34:18.640 --> 00:34:20.120
You are from La Rochelle?

376
00:34:20.920 --> 00:34:21.840
Yes.

377
00:34:22.760 --> 00:34:23.600
What's your name?

378
00:34:24.880 --> 00:34:25.720
Nathalie.

379
00:34:25.800 --> 00:34:27.720
That's nice... suits you.

380
00:34:27.800 --> 00:34:29.440
A beer for my comrade.

381
00:34:30.400 --> 00:34:31.600
Comrade.

382
00:34:34.160 --> 00:34:36.120
That's what it's all about. Team spirit.

383
00:34:38.160 --> 00:34:39.000
You've been upstairs?

384
00:34:39.440 --> 00:34:40.400
For money?

385
00:34:40.720 --> 00:34:41.800
Not really my style.

386
00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:43.200
You're a faggot or what?

387
00:34:43.720 --> 00:34:44.560
No. Why?

388
00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:47.520
You speak French.
you don't like to fuck...

389
00:34:48.800 --> 00:34:50.000
Are you castrated?

390
00:34:57.920 --> 00:35:00.400
Hey. why did you pick this one?

391
00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:05.960
Ouch. I'd rather have a hooker in bed
than a girl somewhere far away.

392
00:35:10.360 --> 00:35:11.200
Cheers.

393
00:35:31.360 --> 00:35:32.520
Are you still in?

394
00:35:44.320 --> 00:35:45.520
Show me.

395
00:36:05.320 --> 00:36:06.160
Nice game.

396
00:36:07.960 --> 00:36:11.160
You fucking asshole. Cheating bastard!

397
00:36:17.600 --> 00:36:18.800
Call the police!

398
00:36:19.320 --> 00:36:20.560
Call the police!

399
00:36:20.680 --> 00:36:24.040
"My deepest condolences
on the passing of your son..."

400
00:36:27.720 --> 00:36:28.560
Come in!

401
00:36:31.240 --> 00:36:34.440
Captain. U-612 is ready
for scheduled departure.

402
00:36:36.720 --> 00:36:37.800
Any problems?

403
00:36:38.560 --> 00:36:39.360
None.

404
00:36:41.400 --> 00:36:42.600
A splendid boat.

405
00:36:46.240 --> 00:36:48.960
I had wondered whether you'd like
to join some of the men.

406
00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.840
As is customary on these occasions.

407
00:36:51.120 --> 00:36:52.960
We needn't be a slave to custom.

408
00:36:53.560 --> 00:36:57.560
Other Captains have felt it benefits
morale to make oneself visible.

409
00:36:57.960 --> 00:37:01.080
I'm sure the men would prefer to do
their drinking and whoring alone.

410
00:37:01.760 --> 00:37:04.880
Wouldn't you?
But we can have a drink together.

411
00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:06.160
First Watch Officer.

412
00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:08.000
Cognac?

413
00:37:08.880 --> 00:37:09.840
Thank you.

414
00:37:14.960 --> 00:37:16.800
HANDBOOK FOR U-BOAT CAPTAINS

415
00:37:16.880 --> 00:37:20.280
Don't tell anyone.
but I haven't finished reading it.

416
00:37:21.760 --> 00:37:24.320
I was just trying to make sense
of paragraph 15.

417
00:37:25.560 --> 00:37:29.920
"During an attack. situations may develop
which appear to be hopeless.

418
00:37:30.240 --> 00:37:33.600
Only if the Captain.
unrelenting towards himself.

419
00:37:33.760 --> 00:37:37.040
conquers this feeling. will he succeed."

420
00:37:37.880 --> 00:37:39.240
A key part of the text.

421
00:37:41.200 --> 00:37:44.360
If the Captain really believes
that a situation is hopeless...

422
00:37:45.880 --> 00:37:47.400
should he risk the lives of his men?

423
00:37:48.600 --> 00:37:50.120
Hopelessness is not a fact...

424
00:37:51.000 --> 00:37:53.280
but a state of mind to be overcome.

425
00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:56.880
The key element is "unrelenting
towards himself".

426
00:38:00.760 --> 00:38:01.960
How is your father?

427
00:38:02.520 --> 00:38:03.560
I hope he's well.

428
00:38:05.400 --> 00:38:06.400
He endures.

429
00:38:07.080 --> 00:38:08.800
I first read his book as a young man.

430
00:38:09.720 --> 00:38:11.840
It's been an inspiration
throughout my career.

431
00:38:12.520 --> 00:38:14.000
How long have you been in the forces?

432
00:38:14.160 --> 00:38:15.120
Since '37.

433
00:38:16.840 --> 00:38:18.080
I don't have your experience.

434
00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:21.240
But you're in command.

435
00:38:22.600 --> 00:38:24.000
The boat is yours.

436
00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:32.160
Good night. Sir.

437
00:39:11.520 --> 00:39:12.600
Frank?

438
00:39:12.680 --> 00:39:13.840
Simone?

439
00:39:14.320 --> 00:39:15.320
Frank?

440
00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:21.440
They say you're sailing tomorrow.

441
00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:23.640
Is that true?

442
00:39:25.600 --> 00:39:26.520
Come with me.

443
00:39:30.680 --> 00:39:32.000
Legs first.

444
00:39:39.400 --> 00:39:41.640
I brought your records.

445
00:39:42.440 --> 00:39:43.600
The records. Thanks.

446
00:39:43.680 --> 00:39:45.000
I thought you'd miss them.

447
00:39:45.360 --> 00:39:46.720
I am screwed.

448
00:39:47.320 --> 00:39:50.000
I have to go.
If not. I'll be court-martialed.

449
00:39:51.600 --> 00:39:54.120
There's something I need you
to do for me. Tonight.

450
00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:55.520
Rue Pernelle 42.

451
00:39:55.600 --> 00:39:57.640
At the corner to Rue Aufredi.

452
00:39:57.720 --> 00:39:58.840
Behind the church.

453
00:39:58.920 --> 00:40:01.720
Shortly before 10:00 p.m.
a woman will show up. Give her this.

454
00:40:02.040 --> 00:40:03.440
There's an envelope in there.

455
00:40:04.200 --> 00:40:05.800
I get something from her in return.

456
00:40:05.920 --> 00:40:09.040
Take it to my private apartment
at this address.

457
00:40:09.640 --> 00:40:12.000
Don't go there in uniform.
Only in civvies.

458
00:40:12.880 --> 00:40:14.240
Is it something illegal?

459
00:40:15.240 --> 00:40:16.680
Tell me that it's nothing illegal!

460
00:40:17.520 --> 00:40:18.880
It's about my life

461
00:40:19.360 --> 00:40:20.720
about everything I have.

462
00:40:22.040 --> 00:40:24.000
I'd do it myself if I...

463
00:40:24.280 --> 00:40:25.320
Christ! What's up?

464
00:40:29.280 --> 00:40:30.160
Sir!

465
00:40:31.320 --> 00:40:34.600
Petty Officer Radio Frank Strasser.
My sister Simone Strasser.

466
00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:39.000
You know that women have no place
on board. Petty Officer Strasser?

467
00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:41.720
Pleased to meet you.

468
00:40:42.720 --> 00:40:44.320
I just came to bring my brothers effects.

469
00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:47.160
I've been assigned at short notice.

470
00:40:47.280 --> 00:40:49.040
For repairs and the war cruise.

471
00:40:49.720 --> 00:40:51.440
There was a fire in the radio room.

472
00:40:53.200 --> 00:40:54.520
A fire?

473
00:40:56.200 --> 00:40:57.600
Yes. this afternoon.

474
00:40:59.680 --> 00:41:01.280
Simone. The Captain is right.

475
00:41:02.000 --> 00:41:03.920
It's bad luck for a woman to be here.

476
00:41:09.400 --> 00:41:10.880
Take care of yourself.

477
00:41:18.960 --> 00:41:20.280
Legs first.

478
00:41:26.560 --> 00:41:27.640
Can you fix this?

479
00:41:29.400 --> 00:41:30.400
I think so.

480
00:41:36.280 --> 00:41:38.520
Well then. see you tomorrow.

481
00:42:02.120 --> 00:42:03.560
He said you were cheating.

482
00:42:04.040 --> 00:42:05.240
I don't understand a word.

483
00:42:14.360 --> 00:42:15.440
- Take him away.
- Sir.

484
00:42:40.920 --> 00:42:41.840
Sorry.

485
00:42:43.160 --> 00:42:46.640
Do you have access to...

486
00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:50.000
coffee... sugar... or cigarettes?

487
00:42:52.280 --> 00:42:53.280
No.

488
00:43:27.960 --> 00:43:30.680
CIRCUIT DIAGRAM OF THE ON-BOARD RADIO-SET

489
00:43:45.560 --> 00:43:46.640
Impossible.

490
00:43:47.200 --> 00:43:48.760
I'm not asking for a pardon.

491
00:43:49.320 --> 00:43:51.040
I'm asking you to suspend
the death penalty.

492
00:43:51.320 --> 00:43:53.120
Why didn't you speak up during the trial?

493
00:43:54.040 --> 00:43:55.400
The opportunity didn't arise.

494
00:43:56.440 --> 00:43:57.760
But I feel responsible.

495
00:43:57.840 --> 00:43:58.680
And rightly so.

496
00:43:58.960 --> 00:44:02.280
This man will be shot tomorrow
because your statement condemned him.

497
00:44:02.760 --> 00:44:04.960
As an officer and now a Captain.

498
00:44:05.040 --> 00:44:07.080
you have to start living
with that responsibility.

499
00:44:07.640 --> 00:44:10.000
That is the power invested
in you by the German Navy.

500
00:44:10.760 --> 00:44:12.400
And what about my power to help him?

501
00:44:13.440 --> 00:44:14.960
To save the life of a fellow crewman?

502
00:44:15.000 --> 00:44:18.720
Hoffmann! Why would you question yourself
in this way? Why now?

503
00:44:18.920 --> 00:44:20.640
Because now I'm expected to command a crew

504
00:44:20.720 --> 00:44:22.960
who probably think the only reason
I've got promoted. is because...

505
00:44:23.080 --> 00:44:24.240
Because?

506
00:44:26.200 --> 00:44:27.320
Because I'm his son.

507
00:44:27.640 --> 00:44:30.800
Because I'm supposed to live up
to his myth. And not because of who I am.

508
00:44:31.400 --> 00:44:34.040
What if I'm not the person
everyone expects me to be?

509
00:44:34.120 --> 00:44:39.120
Hoffmann. Germany needs you to be him.
Precisely because of who you are!

510
00:44:39.320 --> 00:44:42.040
And there's no room for self-doubt.
Not if we want to end this war.

511
00:44:42.680 --> 00:44:43.800
To end it?

512
00:44:45.680 --> 00:44:47.720
This morning it was still
about 'winning it'

513
00:44:51.240 --> 00:44:52.680
This boy dies tomorrow.

514
00:44:53.320 --> 00:44:55.960
If it makes you understand
who you need to be.

515
00:44:56.440 --> 00:44:58.160
then his death will have meaning.

516
00:45:51.280 --> 00:45:52.280
Who are you?

517
00:45:52.360 --> 00:45:54.960
I am supposed to give you something.
From Frank.

518
00:45:55.440 --> 00:45:56.560
I don't know any Frank!

519
00:45:56.840 --> 00:45:58.280
He sent me. I'm his sister.

520
00:45:59.240 --> 00:46:00.440
You've got something for me?

521
00:46:07.760 --> 00:46:10.280
You've got something for me!
Give it to me!

522
00:46:12.520 --> 00:46:13.720
Stop!

523
00:46:13.800 --> 00:46:14.920
Police!

524
00:46:17.680 --> 00:46:18.960
Stop!

525
00:46:20.000 --> 00:46:22.000
Stop. We'll shoot.

526
00:46:23.280 --> 00:46:24.520
Can't see them anymore.

527
00:46:25.200 --> 00:46:27.720
There. there's another one. Stop at once.

528
00:46:27.800 --> 00:46:28.760
Stop!

529
00:46:30.560 --> 00:46:31.360
Stop.

530
00:47:10.240 --> 00:47:11.840
What are you doing here?

531
00:47:12.080 --> 00:47:13.440
Working.

532
00:47:14.000 --> 00:47:15.520
This is the house of the Lord.

533
00:47:16.080 --> 00:47:18.240
You can pray or confess your sins here.

534
00:47:18.640 --> 00:47:20.680
Do you wish to confess your sins. Pierre?

535
00:47:34.440 --> 00:47:35.320
Come with me.

536
00:47:36.040 --> 00:47:37.040
Hurry!

537
00:47:37.560 --> 00:47:39.600
Leave before even more police arrive.

538
00:51:00.320 --> 00:51:02.080
Crew! Attention!

539
00:51:03.720 --> 00:51:07.640
For the report to the Captain. Left face!

540
00:51:18.400 --> 00:51:21.960
First Watch Officer Tennstedt reporting:
Crew lined up for inspection.

541
00:51:30.240 --> 00:51:31.080
At ease!

542
00:51:35.120 --> 00:51:36.600
We are men of the sea.

543
00:51:38.840 --> 00:51:40.920
That means that we have
to confront not only the elements...

544
00:51:41.440 --> 00:51:43.400
but the enemy.

545
00:51:44.680 --> 00:51:46.360
Out there we're on our own.

546
00:51:48.360 --> 00:51:49.520
Gentlemen.

547
00:51:52.080 --> 00:51:53.560
This boat is brand new.

548
00:51:55.680 --> 00:51:56.880
We will test it.

549
00:51:58.720 --> 00:52:00.560
And it will test us.

550
00:52:02.040 --> 00:52:05.280
And in that test be conscious of the man
who stands alongside you.

551
00:52:06.760 --> 00:52:09.000
As there's only one way we will prevail.

552
00:52:10.280 --> 00:52:11.120
Together!

553
00:52:16.440 --> 00:52:17.680
Take her out. First Watch Officer!

554
00:52:21.960 --> 00:52:24.280
What kind of fucking speech was that?

555
00:52:27.680 --> 00:52:29.520
Crew! Attention!

556
00:52:31.040 --> 00:52:32.560
Harbor stations!

557
00:52:32.840 --> 00:52:34.840
Harbor stations!

558
00:53:39.200 --> 00:53:42.080
And so we meet again. Snitch!

559
00:55:17.360 --> 00:55:20.320
She wasn't at the meeting point.
I waited until now.

560
00:55:50.440 --> 00:55:51.920
Last landmark.

561
00:55:58.440 --> 00:56:00.200
Let's see how she does below.

562
00:56:01.880 --> 00:56:02.800
Rig ship for dive.

563
00:56:04.560 --> 00:56:06.400
Rig bridge for dive.

564
00:56:06.520 --> 00:56:07.320
Aye!

565
00:56:08.600 --> 00:56:09.520
Clear the bridge!

566
00:56:19.280 --> 00:56:21.200
The radio equipment
was badly damaged yesterday.

567
00:56:23.040 --> 00:56:24.520
You failed to report this.

568
00:56:27.240 --> 00:56:28.840
The situation was under control.

569
00:56:30.040 --> 00:56:31.760
Then why did you replace
the radio operator?

570
00:56:34.080 --> 00:56:35.280
I didn't deem it...

571
00:56:35.600 --> 00:56:38.120
There was a fire on board and you
didn't tell me. First Watch Officer.

572
00:56:40.080 --> 00:56:42.120
Listen. I don't care how many years
of service you have.

573
00:56:42.520 --> 00:56:43.600
but this is my boat.

574
00:56:45.960 --> 00:56:48.080
I won't tolerate it again. Understood?

575
00:56:50.360 --> 00:56:51.280
Aye. Sir.

576
00:57:10.320 --> 00:57:11.800
Conning tower hatch closed.

577
00:57:15.320 --> 00:57:16.160
Rig buoyancy vents.

578
00:57:16.240 --> 00:57:17.080
Rig buoyancy vents.

579
00:57:19.080 --> 00:57:20.080
Aft buoyancy vent rigged.

580
00:57:20.440 --> 00:57:21.840
Both central buoyancy vents rigged.

581
00:57:21.920 --> 00:57:23.040
All buoyancy vents rigged!

582
00:57:24.000 --> 00:57:25.200
Cycle the vents!

583
00:57:28.520 --> 00:57:29.600
Three zero meters.

584
00:57:30.120 --> 00:57:31.680
Ten degrees dive on the bow planes.

585
00:57:32.240 --> 00:57:34.120
Five degrees dive on the stern planes.

586
00:58:07.760 --> 00:58:09.240
Good morning. Miss Strasser.

587
00:58:09.320 --> 00:58:11.400
Your second day of work
and you're already late?

588
00:58:11.640 --> 00:58:13.120
I slept badly.

589
00:58:13.200 --> 00:58:14.280
I see.

590
00:58:16.080 --> 00:58:17.320
Would you come with me. please?

591
00:58:18.400 --> 00:58:19.240
Why?

592
00:58:20.440 --> 00:58:21.800
I need your help.

593
00:58:37.160 --> 00:58:38.520
This used to be the Customs House.

594
00:58:39.280 --> 00:58:41.280
Now we use it together. the French and us.

595
00:58:42.840 --> 00:58:43.720
Please.

596
00:58:52.440 --> 00:58:53.360
Mr. Duval.

597
00:58:54.240 --> 00:58:57.960
This is Miss Strasser. Mr. Duval is
from the French National Police.

598
00:58:58.000 --> 00:58:59.720
He didn't get much sleep
either last night.

599
00:59:00.000 --> 00:59:01.000
Come with me. please.

600
00:59:01.520 --> 00:59:04.520
I know this is not part
of your normal duties.

601
00:59:04.640 --> 00:59:06.840
but there has been
an incident last night.

602
00:59:07.360 --> 00:59:09.200
probably related to the black market.

603
00:59:09.560 --> 00:59:13.920
Normally Duval takes care of these things
but a French police officer was shot.

604
00:59:14.240 --> 00:59:17.200
He's not sufficiently detached
to be of any big help

605
00:59:17.760 --> 00:59:19.680
and my French is still not
what it should be.

606
00:59:20.720 --> 00:59:22.000
It shouldn't take too long.

606
00:59:23.305 --> 01:00:23.553
